# TgBot Project Context

## What is this

Telegram bot on Go for AI access via OpenAI API. Whitelist authorization, in-memory conversation context.

## Structure

```
cmd/bot/main.go          - entry point
internal/
    config/config.go     - env vars loading
    bot/bot.go           - Telegram handlers
    ai/openai.go         - OpenAI client
    session/session.go   - conversation context (in-memory)
    auth/whitelist.go    - access control
```

## Key Dependencies

- `github.com/go-telegram-bot-api/telegram-bot-api/v5` - Telegram
- `github.com/sashabaranov/go-openai` - OpenAI
- `github.com/joho/godotenv` - .env loading

## Configuration (env vars)

- `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` - bot token
- `OPENAI_API_KEY` - API key
- `OPENAI_MODEL` - model (default: gpt-4o)
- `ALLOWED_USERS` - whitelist user_id comma-separated

## Bot Commands

- `/start` - welcome
- `/new` - clear context
- `/model` - current model
- Text message -> AI response

## Documentation

- Architecture & modules: [ARCHITECTURE.md](mdc:ARCHITECTURE.md)
- Build & deployment: [DEPLOYMENT.md](mdc:DEPLOYMENT.md)

## Coding Conventions

- Indentation: 4 spaces, no tabs
- All output files in English (code, comments, docs)
- README.md always present in project root
- Follow standard Go project structure (cmd/, internal/)
- Secrets only via env vars, never in code
- New AI providers via `ai.Provider` interface
- Thread-safe access to shared state via mutex
